53.7	Visual_impairment	Visual impairment	Visual impairment (or vision impairment) is vision loss (of a person) to such a degree as to qualify as an additional support need through a significant limitation of visual capability resulting from either disease, trauma, or congenital or degenerative conditions that cannot be corrected by conventional means, such as refractive correction, medication, or surgery. This functional loss of vision is typically defined to manifest with	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Hyperopia.gif/230px-Hyperopia.gif
